13. HƯỚNG DẪN TIẾP TỤC DỰ ÁN

13.1 Setup Environment
    
    cd PrinterDuplexScanForCheapPrint
    
    # Activate virtual environment
    # Windows:
    .venv\Scripts\activate
    # Linux:
    source .venv/bin/activate
    
    # Verify dependencies
    pip list
    
    # Run tests để verify current state
    python tests/run_unit_tests.py
    python integration_tests.py

13.2 Priority Implementation Order
    
    Priority 1: scan_document Mode
    - Đây là feature phức tạp nhất
    - Cần nhiều testing
    - Quan trọng cho use case "scan nhiều document nhỏ"
    
    Priority 2: card_2in1 Mode
    - Đơn giản hơn scan_document
    - Use case rõ ràng (CCCD, thẻ)
    - Có thể reuse code từ PDF generator
    
    Priority 3: Session Management Advanced ✅ COMPLETED
    - ✅ Timeout handling implemented với threading
    - ✅ Session switching với suspend/revive logic
    - ✅ Automatic cleanup sau timeout
    - ✅ Thread-safe operations
    
    Priority 4: Deployment
    - Test trên Linux VM trước
    - Sau đó deploy lên Raspberry Pi
    - CUPS configuration cần careful testing
    
    Priority 5: Production Features
    - Logging, error handling, cleanup
    - Monitoring và performance tuning
    - Documentation cho end users

13.3 Testing Strategy
    
    1. Implement feature
    2. Write unit tests (tests/test_*.py)
    3. Add integration test (integration_tests.py)
    4. Test với real images
    5. Verify trên target hardware
    6. Document behavior

13.4 Debug Tips
    
    # Enable test mode để không xóa files
    config.yaml:
      test_mode: true
    
    # Xem detailed logs
    python src/main.py  # có detailed per-image logging
    
    # Test individual functions
    python -m tests.test_orientation
    python -m tests.test_deskew
    
    # Create debug scripts khi cần
    # Example: debug_orientation.py, visualize_deskew.py

13.5 Code Style
    
    - Type hints cho function parameters
    - Docstrings cho public functions
    - Clear variable names
    - Comments cho complex logic
    - Keep functions focused (single responsibility)

13.6 Git Workflow (nếu dùng)
    
    - Branch cho mỗi feature: feature/scan-document
    - Commit nhỏ, clear messages
    - Test trước khi merge
    - Tag releases: v0.1.0, v0.2.0

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

14. KNOWN ISSUES & SOLUTIONS

14.1 Orientation Detection
    
    Issue: Uniform content (single letter O/H) detected incorrectly
    Solution: ✅ Implemented batch voting với threshold 0.60
    
    Issue: Individual confidence quá thấp
    Solution: ✅ Batch override khi >60% ảnh cùng kết quả

14.2 Deskew Correction
    
    Issue: Deskew xoay sai chiều (làm tệ hơn)
    Solution: ✅ Fixed rotation direction: img.rotate(angle) thay vì -angle
    
    Issue: Blank pages bị deskew không cần thiết
    Solution: ✅ Detect blank (intensity>240, density<0.02) → return 0°

14.3 Performance
    
    Issue: PDF generation chậm với ReportLab
    Solution: ✅ Migrated to PyMuPDF (fitz)
      - 5-20x faster than ReportLab
      - In-memory buffers (no temp files)
      - C++ backend for speed
      - scan_duplex: ~2-3s cho 10 pages
      - scan_document: ~7s cho 32 documents/13 pages
    
    Issue: OpenCV operations chậm trên Raspberry Pi
    Solution: ⏳ Chưa test, có thể cần optimize:
      - Resize ảnh trước khi process (✅ đã có _optimize_for_pdf)
      - Skip expensive operations nếu confidence cao
      - Batch processing với threading

14.4 Testing
    
    Issue: Không có cách generic để chạy multiple tests
    Solution: ✅ Tạo test framework với TestCase/TestSuite classes

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

15. TECHNICAL DECISIONS & RATIONALE

15.1 Why Python?
    - Rich libraries: OpenCV, Pillow, ReportLab
    - Fast prototyping
    - Good enough performance cho Raspberry Pi
    - Easy deployment (no compilation)

15.2 Why Edge-based Orientation Detection?
    - SOTA method cho document images
    - Không cần training data
    - Robust với various content types
    - Fast enough cho real-time processing

15.3 Why Batch Voting?
    - Handle uniform content (single letters)
    - More robust than individual decisions
    - Reflects real scanning behavior (consistent orientation)

15.4 Why Separate Fronts/Backs?
    - ADF simplex scanner limitation
    - User scans fronts first, then flips and scans backs
    - Need to reverse backs order for correct pairing

15.5 Why Test Mode?
    - Essential for development
    - Prevents accidental file deletion
    - Allows inspection of intermediate results
    - Safe testing without printer

15.6 Why Not Auto-Center for scan_document?
    - Respect user intent
    - Predictable behavior
    - No AI guessing
    - User controls layout physically

